# Two jobs in one file:
#
# (1) Real exclusions for every uv-tool project under this directory —
#     virtualenvs created by `uv sync`, Python bytecode caches.
#
# (2) Block hatchling's upward `.gitignore` walk. Hatchling's
#     `locate_file(root, ".gitignore", boundary=".git")` walks UP from a
#     project root until it finds a `.gitignore` OR a `.git/` directory OR
#     hits the filesystem root. With no `.git/` anywhere up the path and a
#     populated `~/.gitignore` (which exists on this machine), the walk
#     reaches `~/.gitignore`, applies its patterns to our project tree, and
#     SILENTLY produces an empty wheel — `uv tool install` succeeds, the shim
#     runs, but `import <package>` fails with `ModuleNotFoundError`.
#     This file's existence makes hatchling stop here, so `~/.gitignore` is
#     never read. See ./README.md for the full story.

# uv virtualenv (regenerated by `uv sync`)
.venv/

**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
